-- South African Opposition Says it May Seek a Probe of ArcelorMittal Deal
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2010-10-06T10:01:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/south-african-opposition-says-it-may-seek-a-probe-of-arcelormittal-deal.html
South Africa’s opposition Democratic
Alliance party said it will ask the country’s Financial Services
Board to investigate the sale of a stake in ArcelorMittal South
Africa Ltd. to investors including a son of President Jacob Zuma
if the deal is approved.  The Democratic Alliance commented in an e-mailed statement
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  